--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This role manages freebsd_pkg.

FreeBSD package management tool. Pkg provides an interface for manipulating
packages: registering, adding, removing and upgrading packages.

For more detailed information on the usage and available configuration options
please consult the following sections.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
USAGE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL
  - hosts: all
    roles:
      - role: freebsd_pkg
    vars:
      freebsd_pkg_state: 'install'

REMOVE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
      - role: freebsd_pkg
    vars:
      freebsd_pkg_state: 'remove'

INACTIVE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
      - role: freebsd_pkg
    vars:
      freebsd_pkg_state: 'inactive'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
VARIABLES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ROLE
  freebsd_pkg_state
    Description: Control the state of the role.
    Implemented: 0.1
    Required   : False
    Value      : Predetermined
    Type       : String
    Default    : 'install'
    Options    :
      Install : 'true' | 'yes' | 'install'
      Remove  : 'false' | 'no' | 'remove'
      Inactive: 'quiesce' | 'inactive'

  freebsd_pkg_pkg_conf_template
    Description: Define the template source for 'pkg.conf.j2'.
                 Any value other than 'default' requires a Jinja2 file to be
                 created. The custom Jinja2 file for an example configuration
                 called 'example' needs to be placed as follows:
                 'freebsd_pkg/templates/example/pkg.conf.j2'
    Implemented: 0.1
    Required   : False
    Value      : Arbitrary
    Type       : String
    Default    : 'default'
    Options    :
      Examples: 'example' | 'environment' | 'hostname'

